                <h1>Understanding the Nazis: Origins and Impact</h1>
                <p>The Nazis were a far-right political party in Germany, led by Adolf Hitler from 1920 to 1945. They promoted extreme nationalism, anti-Semitism, and totalitarianism, resulting in widespread persecution and the Holocaust. Their regime instigated World War II, leading to immense destruction and loss of life across Europe.</p>
